          <h4>Main Work Responsibilities:</h4>
          <p>Manage existing spec in the PLM system. Work closely with other technical designers, creative designers, and retailers to maintain consistency and integrity of fit. Maintain quality standards through live fittings and technical spec packages.</p>
          <p>Responsible for technical design process from initial development to final fit for a broad classification of men’s, junior’s, and children’s sleepwear products. New product processes include: creating technical sketches with Adobe products (Illustrator, etc.), create grade tables, determine measurements according to proper fitting, construction details, etc.</p> 
          <p>Provide support to the graphic design team and production artists with samples and graded sizes to determine the print or art size.</p>
          <p>Utilize Gerber and Optitex software to manipulate the pattern improve fitting. This process can include creating a new pattern or altering an existing pattern to send to the factory for production.</p>
